The paper discusses differential privacy, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). It also involves data analysis and storage, which are topics in databases (cs.DB). The use of tf-idf estimation and machine learning models for analysis suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a new model for centralized differential privacy, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
